<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1248">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source"><hi rend="smallcaps"><persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers</hi></note>
                                <head>No. 1248<lb/><hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from">Truman</persName> to Prime
                                        Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract<note n="1" xml:id="d1248fn1">For the other paragraphs of this letter, see <ref target="#d1183">document No.
                                        1183</ref>.</note>]</seg>
                                </opener>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-25">July 25,
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Prime Minister</hi>: …</p>
                                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                                <p>We sent you last night a copy of our telegram to <persName corresp="#p_CK1">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d1248fn2">See <ref target="#d1246">document No.
                                            1246</ref>.</note> I am hoping that we will receive a
                                    concurrence from him, and that we may be in a position to issue
                                    the Proclamation at the earliest possible moment. I shall inform
                                    you, as soon as I hear from him, and we will issue the
                                    Proclamation jointly from here, if that is satisfactory to
                                    you.</p>
                                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                                <closer><signed>[<persName corresp="#p_THS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Harry S. Truman</hi></persName>]</signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>